Paniai has always been a sick place for the Indonesian government.
The lack of meaningful development is caused by discontent among the Mei, Moni, Dani and Damal tribes scattered throughout the greened central highlands of Papua.
Many joined the Papua Free Movement (OPM), a rebel army that claims to defend the rights of the Papuas by launching sporadic attacks and raids on Indonesian soldiers.
