"Now foreign journalists trying to report from rebel eastern Indonesian provinces, Papua and West Papua, face new dangers: visa denials and blacklisting," he said in a statement.
The lack of media attention means that international pressure on the Indonesian Government is largely limited to Papua's immediate neighbours.
In March, six Pacific States – Tonga, Nauru, Palau, Tuvalu, the Marshall Islands, and Solomon Islands – requested the UN Human Rights Council to investigate “various and widespread violations” in Papua, including shooting in Paniai.
