In addition, the text made it clear that restrictions on the holding of certain positions for foreigners would not apply to those who had renounced “other” citizenship in writing and had submitted a previous passport to the Ministry of Internal Affairs, but “for reasons beyond its control” he had not ceased to be considered a citizen of another country.
Foreigners are now prohibited from holding positions in the municipal service and from being recruited to work in facilities and organizations whose activities are related to the security of Russia.
Nor may a person with dual citizenship or a residence permit of another country become a member of the State Duma or a member of the Council of the Federation.
