The Government approved the establishment of a cultural policy commission
The Russian Government has approved the establishment of a commission on State cultural policy.
The relevant regulation has been published on the Government website.
According to the document, the main task of the commission will be to develop and adjust strategic approaches to the implementation of cultural policies.
The Commission will also draft a cultural policy strategy, clarify objectives and prepare new programmes for its implementation.
The head of the commission has been appointed Vice-President of the Government of the Russian Federation.
