The Prime Minister of the Russian Federation, Dmitry Medvedev, approved in 2016 a plan for the implementation of the State cultural policy strategy until 2030.
The plan includes 193 activities and includes measures to expand the influence of Russian culture in other countries, preserve a unified cultural space and cultural heritage, and contribute to the creation of conditions for the development of culture in the country.
