In Ukraine, Russians were asked to be sent to prison for illegal border crossing
The Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine has registered a draft law under which Russians may be subject to criminal sanctions for illegally crossing the Ukrainian border.
According to RT, a document registered in the electronic database of the Ukrainian Parliament implies a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens attempting to enter the country illegally.
It is noted that for a repeat offence or an act committed by a group of persons, the sentence may be increased to five years.
If, however, the perpetrator was detained at the border with the weapon, the time of detention for him would increase to eight years.
It was previously reported that Ukrainian border guards had detained Ukrainians attempting to enter Russia outside the designated crossing points.
