In Moscow, a police officer shot a man in the leg, defending himself from assault.
A police officer shot a member of a fight in Moscow in the leg after he attacked him with a piece of glass in his hand.
On 3 August, the police department of the Russian Ministry of Internal Affairs for the Yakimana district received a report of a fight on Motnay Street, 46.
"Arrived police outfit stopped the offence and separated the parties to the conflict," reported RIA News with a reference to the press service of the capital head of the Ministry of Internal Affairs.
According to the police, when one of the parties to the conflict attacked a member of the Ministry of Internal Affairs with a piece of glass, a police officer warned the man several times about the use of a weapon and fired a warning shot.
This did not stop the bully, after which a law enforcement officer shot a man in the leg.
The wounded man needed hospitalization.
